originalText.text: It smells so good in here! I decided to stop by and give them a try after my Ma kept raving about their tasty baked goods. I purchased three different cookies and they were absolutely delicious. Prices are reasonable and staff are so nice.

text.text: It smells so good in here! I decided to stop by and give them a try after my Ma kept raving about their tasty baked goods. I purchased three different cookies and they were absolutely delicious. Prices are reasonable and staff are so nice.

originalText.text:
Innovating the cookie game!

Part cookie, part pie - I was confused at the start. Let me break it down for you (no pun intended).

The bottom of the pie crust cookie is where the “pie” part comes in. It is a disc of pie crust. The kind that is flaky and in layers.

On top you have their cookie dough that forms the shell.

Inside the shell, there is a filling, just like a pie! I got a chocolate one which had a filling similar to a ganache.

I also got the cream cheese guava one which was filled with exactly what it sounds like. On the outside of this cookie was a sugar cookie type dough.

I also got a classic cookie to try it out. I believe it was the butter toffee and it was great! Buttery. Rich toffee flavor. Came right from the oven so they had to see if they were cool enough to serve. The freshest a cookie can be! Yum.

I appreciate they bake everything right there on site. It also looks like they package their cookies. I’d imagine these are sold in stores? Looked like they were preparing gift boxes. Great idea!

I’ll be back for more treats!

originalText.text: I just spent six dollars on a cookie. Was it financially responsible? No. Was it worth the $6, yes. Would I do it again? I’m already looking at the menu; this stuff is addicting (if you’re on a diet just close your eyes and treat yourself). I won’t be brushing my teeth tonight just to savor the taste, that’ll be a problem for my dentist - not me. Janie, I don’t know who you are but I love you and I love this delicious half baked chocolate chip cookie you made. Thank you for encouraging me to be irresponsible— yet so very happy.

originalText.text: I am OBSESSED with everything we have ever ordered here. Any of the pie crust cookies are incredible. The chocolate chip cookies are baked perfectly. Crunchy on the outside and decadent on the inside.

originalText.text: I participated in the TooGoodToGo program for the 2nd avenue location. I was looking forward to trying her pastries after hearing about the owners story. However I will never try them again. The pastries I received were missing pieces and broken. The bag I received the pastries in had soaked up so much grease from the pastries that it was practically falling apart.  Thankfully I had brought another bag with me otherwise the pastries would have fallen all over. I paid 7$ for a 21$ worth bag. I unfortunately could not eat anything due to it being so greasy looking and the broken pieces were off putting.I know that TooGoodToGo’s message is fighting food waste. However, everything  I received should have been tossed to the garbage not given to customers this is not what the program is about.  Very disappointed. If I could give it zero stars I would.
